HEADWORD: Dour
<hw>Dour</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>dur</ets>,
L. <ets>durus</ets>.]</ety> <def>Hard; inflexible; obstinate; sour in
aspect; hardy; bold.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>dour</qex> wife, a sour old carlin.</q> <rj><qau>C.
Reade.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

